{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An instruction-tuned model is a base model that has been further trained on a dataset of (instruction, response) pairs so that it reliably executes directives rather than continuing text. Where a base model given \"Summarise the following article:\" might add more articles, an instruction-tuned model produces a summary. This behavioural shift — from text completion to instruction execution — is what makes foundation models practically useful. Instruction-tuned models are the default choice for nearly all applications; base models are used mainly for research or as the starting point for custom fine-tuning."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {"level": 2},
        "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Instruction Tuning Changes the Model"}]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Instruction tuning does not add new knowledge — the factual content of the model's weights is largely unchanged. What changes is the distribution the model samples from. Before tuning, the model assigns high probability to text that looks like pretraining data (internet text, books, code). After tuning, it assigns high probability to text that looks like a competent human response to the given instruction."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]},
              {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Base model"}]}]},
              {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Instruction-tuned model"}]}]}
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Response to \"Summarise X\""}]}]},
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "May continue the prompt or generate more text"}]}]},
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Produces a summary"}]}]}
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Factual knowledge"}]}]},
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Same"}]}]},
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Same (not increased by IFT)"}]}]}
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stops generating at appropriate point"}]}]},
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Often does not; keeps producing text"}]}]},
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes — learns to stop after completing the task"}]}]}
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Follows format constraints"}]}]},
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Unreliable"}]}]},
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reliable for common formats (JSON, bullet lists, etc.)"}]}]}
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Declines harmful requests"}]}]},
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No — completes any continuation"}]}]},
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Partial (depends on safety training beyond IFT)"}]}]}
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use in production"}]}]},
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rare — usually a starting point for further FT"}]}]},
              {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard for most applications"}]}]}
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {"level": 2},
        "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using an Instruction-Tuned Model via API"}]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {"language": "python"},
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\n\ndef run_instruction(instruction: str, content: str = \"\") -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Execute a natural-language instruction on optional content.\n    The model has been instruction-tuned and interprets the\n    message as a directive, not as text to continue.\n    \"\"\"\n    user_message = instruction if not content else f\"{instruction}\\n\\n{content}\"\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-opus-4-8\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_message}],\n    )\n    return response.content[0].text\n\n\n# Tasks that a base model handles poorly but an instruction-tuned model handles well:\n\n# 1. Format conversion\ncsv_data = \"name,age,city\\nAlice,30,London\\nBob,25,Paris\"\nprint(run_instruction(\n    \"Convert this CSV to a Markdown table.\",\n    csv_data\n))\n\n# 2. Extraction\narticle = \"The merger between Alpha Corp and Beta Inc was announced on June 3rd ...\"\nprint(run_instruction(\n    \"Extract all company names and dates from this text. Return JSON: {\\\"companies\\\": [], \\\"dates\\\": []}.\",\n    article\n))\n\n# 3. Multi-step task\nprint(run_instruction(\n    \"Write a Python function that checks if a string is a palindrome. \"\n    \"Include type hints and a docstring.\"\n))\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {"level": 2},
        "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Open-Weight Instruction-Tuned Models"}]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every major open-weight base model has a corresponding instruction-tuned variant, released alongside it. The naming convention varies by family:"
          }
        ]
      },
