        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {"level": 2},
        "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use a Base Model Instead"}]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Choose the base model when:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [
              {"type": "text", "text": "You are creating a custom instruction-following dataset and do not want the existing instruction-tuning to bias the continuations."}
            ]}]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [
              {"type": "text", "text": "You need log-probabilities for scoring or ranking candidate completions, and the instruction-tuned model's style would skew the scores."}
            ]}]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [
              {"type": "text", "text": "You are doing full fine-tuning for a highly specialised task (e.g. clinical note generation) and want to avoid having to un-learn the general instruction-following style."}
            ]}]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [
              {"type": "text", "text": "You are studying the base model's representations for research purposes (probing, mechanistic interpretability)."}
            ]}]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The instruction-tuned model is not a smarter version of the base model — it is a differently steered version. The knowledge is the same; the probability mass has been redistributed toward helpful, task-completing outputs."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
